FBIS4-59344 "drnes092_j_94040" FBIS-NES-94-092 Daily Report 11 May 1994 ARABIAN PENINSULA Yemen Presidential Council Member Inspects Missile Explosion Site Presidential Council Member Inspects Missile Explosion Site JN1105151194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network in Arabic 1400 GMT 11 May 94 JN1105151194 Sanaa Yemeni Republic Radio Network Arabic BFN [Text] Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani, member of the Presidential Council, has met with the brother directors of the administrations of the Presidential Council Office and several advisers, in the presence of brother Lieutenant General Sa'id Muhammad Ghanim, deputy chairman of the General Staff Command. Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani reviewed the stages of the development of the fabricated crisis and the [word indistinct] the secessionist leadership of the Yemeni Socialist Party [YSP] of declaring war at more than one location. He pointed out that the objective of that leadership is to fragment national unity by inciting regional loyalties, stressing that the Yemeni people in all governorates are now aware of the conspiracy, especially after that leadership has rejected legitimacy and revealed its deep-rooted malice against defenseless citizens. The brother member of the Presidential Council said all the concessions offered to the YSP did not change their sick, odious mentalities [words indistinct]. They continued to reject Islamic law as a frame of reference [words indistinct] a winery, and would not implement the decisions of the authorities to turn this winery, that violates the orders of God in broad daylight, into another factory that is useful to the citizens [words indistinct]. Shaykh 'Abd-al-Majid al-Zandani also inspected the situation of the people at the site of the ugly, odious crime committed by the forces of apostasy and secession when a missile fell on the homes of secure citizens. The member of the Presidential Council delivered a speech to a massive crowd that had flocked since early morning to the scene of the crime. He aid the enemies of unity and democracy have used the weapon the Yemeni people bought with their [word indistinct] and sweat. He said the Yemeni people in the southern governorates have suffered for 23 years and paid a heavy price as a result of malice and tyranny.
